one d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526490\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cks1665702588253.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cks1665702588253.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cks1665702588253.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cks1665702588253\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Styling Entities and Occurrences in HTML\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When Uniface generates HTML for dynamic server pages (DSPs), it sets HTML class attributes that can be used to style the server page.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cks1665702588253__section_w1026ab1b5b1_w1027ab1b5_w1028ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d637382e51\">\n                        \n Empty Occurrences and Entities\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cks1665702588253__p_d20723e1_d20724e1_d20725e1\">If no data is present in a component, Uniface generates a default empty occurrence for each entity in a DSP and flags it as empty. Uniface class attributes are applied to the HTML elements representing the empty entity and occurrence. This enables you to define a CSS to suppress or otherwise format the empty elements.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Empty Element and Occurrence Classes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__1\">\n Uniface Class Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__2\">\n Applicable To\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__3\">\n Styling Example\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-uocc-empty-</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__2\">\n Empty occurrences\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__3\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.-uocc-empty- { visibility: hidden;\n                           }</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-uent-empty-</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__2\">\n Entity with only one occurrence, which is empty\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cks1665702588253__table_d2369e1_d2370e1_d2371e1__entry__3\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.-uent-empty- { visibility: hidden;\n                           }</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cks1665702588253__p_d20726e1_d20727e1_d20728e1\">An occurrence (and its parent entity) is flagged as empty in the following circumstances:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9944e1_d9945e1_d9946e1\">It is the default occurrence.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9947e1_d9948e1_d9949e1\">It is the last occurrence and it has been removed or discarded in ProcScript (by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">remocc</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">discard</span>), or in JavaScript (by <span class=\"keyword apiname\">OccurrenceObject.remove()</span> or <span class=\"keyword apiname\">OccurrenceObject.discard()</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9950e1_d9951e1_d9952e1\">The entity has been cleared in ProcScript by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">clear</span> or in JavaScript by <span class=\"keyword apiname\">EntityObject.clear()</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cks1665702588253__p_d20729e1_d20730e1_d20731e1\">The status of an empty occurrence changes in the following circumstances:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9953e1_d9954e1_d9955e1\">The end-user enters data in a field and leaves the field.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9956e1_d9957e1_d9958e1\">A value is assigned to a field in ProcScript or JavaScript (using <span class=\"keyword apiname\">FieldObject.setValue()</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cks1665702588253__li_d9959e1_d9960e1_d9961e1\">A new occurrence is added or created in ProcScript\n               (by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">creocc</span>) or in JavaScript (by\n                  <span class=\"keyword apiname\">EntityObject.createOccurrence()</span>,\n                  <span class=\"keyword apiname\">OccurrenceObject.insertNewAfter()</span>, or\n                  <span class=\"keyword apiname\">OccurrenceObject.insertNewBefore()</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"cks1665702588253__note_w1029ab1b5b1c15_w1030ab1b5b1_w1031ab1b5_w1032ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When the status of an inner entity changes from empty to non-empty, this change is also applied to its parent outer entity (or entities).</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqr1719489288111.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entity and Occurrence Properties in Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>In Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the widget properties of entities and occurrences in the runtime component using ProcScript or JavaScript. It is not possible to set these properties declaratively.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526490\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526490\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Styling Entities and Occurrences in HTML Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Styling Entities and Occurrences in HTML When Uniface generates HTML for dynamic server pages (DSPs), it sets HTML class attributes that can be used to style the server page. Empty Occurrences and Entities If no data is present in a component, Uniface generates a default empty occurrence for each entity in a DSP and flags it as empty. Uniface class attributes are applied to the HTML elements representing the empty entity and occurrence. This enables you to define a CSS to suppress or otherwise format the empty elements. Table 1. Empty Element and Occurrence Classes Uniface Class Name Applicable To Styling Example -uocc-empty- Empty occurrences .-uocc-empty- { visibility: hidden; } -uent-empty- Entity with only one occurrence, which is empty .-uent-empty- { visibility: hidden; } An occurrence (and its parent entity) is flagged as empty in the following circumstances: It is the default occurrence. It is the last occurrence and it has been removed or discarded in ProcScript (by remocc or discard ), or in JavaScript (by OccurrenceObject.remove() or OccurrenceObject.discard() ) The entity has been cleared in ProcScript by clear or in JavaScript by EntityObject.clear() . The status of an empty occurrence changes in the following circumstances: The end-user enters data in a field and leaves the field. A value is assigned to a field in ProcScript or JavaScript (using FieldObject.setValue() ) A new occurrence is added or created in ProcScript (by creocc ) or in JavaScript (by EntityObject.createOccurrence() , OccurrenceObject.insertNewAfter() , or OccurrenceObject.insertNewBefore() Note: When the status of an inner entity changes from empty to non-empty, this change is also applied to its parent outer entity (or entities). Related Links Entity and Occurrence Properties in Dynamic Server Pages In Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the widget properties of entities and occurrences in the runtime component using ProcScript or JavaScript. It is not possible to set these properties declaratively. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}